  "page": "Morne",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For other usage, see <a href=\"/index.php/Morne_(disambiguation)\" title=\"Morne (disambiguation)\">Morne (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\n<p><b>Morne</b> was the seat of petty kings who ruled from the eastern shore of <a href=\"/index.php/Tarth\" title=\"Tarth\">Tarth</a> in what is now the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a>. Having examined the castle's ruins, Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Hubert\" title=\"Hubert\">Hubert</a> writes in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Kin_of_the_Stag\" title=\"Kin of the Stag\">Kin of the Stag</a></i> that Morne was of <a href=\"/index.php/Andals\" title=\"Andals\">Andal</a> origin, not <a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a>. Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Galladon_of_Morne\" title=\"Galladon of Morne\">Galladon of Morne</a> is a legendary <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> of the island.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Morne&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D